reviews.author: John Linnane
reviews.comment: David was great! I called on a whim because I needed a faucet replaced. He had a cancellation and turned up within the hour, replaced the faucet and some other 50 year old parts all within a couple of hours for a great price. He's a great guy too and I highly recommend him.

reviews.author: Matthew Calamito
reviews.comment: PSR is top notch, professional, timely, and honest. They have helped out on numerous occasions and fixed any issues that other plumbers could not. David Dobbs is honest and provided information as to what went wrong and what he is doing to address the fix while teaching you along the way. I will only continue to use PSR!

reviews.author: Jon Karnofsky
reviews.comment: I've had them help two times now, each with multiple issues. I consider them knowledge, fair, reasonably priced, and willing to show me things I can do myself in the future.

reviews.author: Mary Kathryn Kurth
reviews.comment: David is great! He s done multiple jobs at our house and is always punctual, professional and his prices are reasonable. He also guarantees his work which is reassuring. The work he has done for us has always been as quoted or less than the quote which shows his integrity and honesty! He has come to our house promptly for emergencies too. Can t recommend David enough!

reviews.author: Tony P.
reviews.comment: I saw excellent reviews about David on Next Door and called him to fix a leaky faucet. He came to my home that night a fixed it quickly at a minimum charge.  I recently needed to exchange a bath and shower with a new walk-in shower without having to pay for an expensive re modeling job.  He came by the week I called, took measurements, and had the job done by the next week.  The shower is just what I wanted. He was always courteous and knows plumbing. I trust him to get the job done right and confidently recommend him. Services:   Faucet repair ,  Shower repair Services:   Faucet repair ,  Shower repair

reviews.author: bill burroughs
reviews.comment: This company showed up on time and replaced a mixing valve for a shower.  They were very friendly and very professional.  The repair was completed in a timely and competent manner.  When I needed an adjustment almost a year later within that warranty period they answered the phone promptly and came back within a few days as agreed.  They made the additional adjustments to my satisfaction with no additional charges.  In an era when it is so difficult to find someone you can trust and is professional and honors their warranty, this company checks all those boxes.  I will definitely call them again for additional plumbing needs.  Bill Service:   Faucet installation Service:   Faucet installation

reviews.author: Bill Hopwood
reviews.comment: I was looking for a highly-rated, independent plumber in North Raleigh to replace my water heater.  David promptly returned my call, was very accommodative with my schedule, and arrived when he said he would.  David is affable, reasonably priced, and competent in his trade.  I will use David at Plumbing Services of Raleigh again and I recommend him for plumbing repairs without hesitation.

reviews.author: Jennifer Torres
reviews.comment: I contacted David's office the day before NYE requesting him to check for leaks as my water bill has gone up significantly. David came out the very next day (New Years) just to reassure me before the long weekend. His fee was more than reasonable and he was prompt and efficient. He also took the time to show me what he was seeing so I could have a better understanding. I will be referring David to anyone who is in need of a quality plumber who will not rip you off.

reviews.author: Maureen OMeara
reviews.comment: David was a life saver!  Today, on a Sunday, we had sewage water spewing out of the powder room toilet.  He responded to us so quickly!  He assessed the problem and cleared the clog completely, inside and in the crawl space.  This is not the first time he has solved our plumbing problems.  Always professional and such a pleasure to work with.  We trust him completely!!  We highly recommend him! Service:   Drain cleaning Service:   Drain cleaning

reviews.author: Emily Berry
reviews.comment: David did an awesome job with our emergency plumbing problem! He came out quickly, worked to solve a tough problem that kept throwing him curveballs and get us back up and running within a few hours. Would definitely recommend and use again!

reviews.author: Chris Moyer
reviews.comment: I was recently a first time customer of David Dobbs plumbing and while I hope to not need their services anytime soon, I will definitely be a repeat customer! The service was fantastic, and the thing that I appreciate most is how hard David worked to save me as much money as possible which DEFINITELY builds trust and makes me more ok spending money on the things that he recommends. I called thinking I needed a hot water heater replacement and what he sold me on was a much simpler solution. I highly recommend him! Services:   Plumbing leak detection ,  Plumbing pipe repair Services:   Plumbing leak detection ,  Plumbing pipe repair

reviews.author: Khoi
reviews.comment: Had a pipe burst in the ceiling wall when I came home from work late at night.  Called Plumbing Services of Raleigh the very next day and talked to David, and he literally showed up 7 minutes later.  No Joke.  He located the broken pipe, and explained the situation in detail about why it happened and answered all of my questions.  I was actually exhausted from the night before (from being waterless) and had not thought much about the pricing, but it was very competitive.  It was a great surprise since I've used other plumbing companies before.  Can't say thank you enough. Services:   Plumbing leak detection ,  Plumbing leak repair Services:   Plumbing leak detection ,  Plumbing leak repair

reviews.author: Mark Price
reviews.comment: David with Plumbing Services of Raleigh has handled several plumbing issues we've needed at our house in Raleigh.  Service is top notch, pricing is clear and fair, happy to recommend. Service:   Water heater repair Service:   Water heater repair

reviews.author: Chase Andrews
reviews.comment: I highly recommend Plumbing Services of Raleigh! David goes out of his way to always provide the highest quality of work at phenomenal rates. My wife and I were remodeling our home and David completed several projects at our house which included moving our kitchen sink, capping off a water line, installing a new bathtub, and installing a bathroom vanity. In addition there was a large noise of rattling pipes in our home whenever we used the washing machine or outdoor hoses. He was able to tell us the problem within seconds and fix it at a low cost. David was always willing to answer any questions that I had and educate me when I asked. I will always use Plumbing Services of Raleigh! Services:   Shower installation ,  Plumbing pipe repair ,  Toilet installation ,  Faucet installation Services:   Shower installation ,  Plumbing pipe repair ,  Toilet installation ,  Faucet installation

reviews.author: Chris Grainger
reviews.comment: David supported me in Home Depot to help select the right material for a project I was working on.  He even gave me his number and told me to call if I had questions. Well I did and after several text messages and advice I was able to complete the project. When someone helps you just to be helpful says all I need to know about their character. I highly recommend working with David and will be calling him in the future when needed. You re in good hands here.

reviews.author: Meghan W
reviews.comment: David installed a new kitchen sink, faucet, and reconnected my garbage disposal and did very high quality work!  Very responsive, honest, explained every detail (I had a lot of questions- and it was not an easy job).  He is my first call with anything plumbing related! Thank you David!! Services:   Garbage disposal installation ,  Faucet repair ,  Faucet installation Services:   Garbage disposal installation ,  Faucet repair ,  Faucet installation

reviews.author: Austin Stith
reviews.comment: David Dobbs installed a new water heater for me earlier today. reviews.comment: Pros: I called for an emergency leaking pipe in my crawlspace, and they got it fixed the same day. Cons: They were ~3 hours late (scheduled for 6pm, showed up at 9PM). They charged me an emergency after-hours fee (after being late) After assessing the situation, they made a series of demonstrably false statements (I have photographic evidence to counter them all) to suggest the purchase of more expensive services, including that: 1.  My water pressure was 110PSI (my gauge later read 97PSI) 2. I do not have a water-pressure reducing valve installed on my house (I do - it may not be working properly, but it is clearly visible from the area the plumber was working in) 3. The supply line from the meter to the house is made of PB and likely to burst (it is made of PEX, transitioning to PB in the house. This is also clearly visible from where the plumber was working) I would recommend getting a second opinion before committing to any services this enterprise recommends..
